Notes on HTML

<html>
	<head>
		<title> Span tag demo </title>
		<style type ="text/css">
		span
		{
			color:red;
			font-weight:bold;
			font-style:italic;
			text-decoration:underline;
		}
	</head>
	
	<body>
	
	<span>Hello World</span>
	
	</body>

</html>


Div tab - Block level tag - Start from fresh line and take entire available width on page. It divides the page into different section.
span tab -inline tag - Takes only width which is required to display the content.

Now it is now recommended to apply style (ex. <font color> <u> <i> <b> inside body tag. insted use span tag in body and apply style in head tag



<ul> - Unordered list tag, block level tag
<li> - list item tag, block level tag



JavaScript is client side scripting language and written insidehtml file

Server side language don't send the code to the user but only output

Java and Java Script are different language. 


html>
	<head>
		<title> demo </title>
	</head>
	
	<body>
		<script>
		document.write("Hello World");
		var myvariable = false;
		
		var words = "This is"
		var morewords = "a sentence";
		var sentence = words + morewords;
		document.write(sentence);
		
		var lengeth = sentence.length;
		var result = sentence.substring(2,3)
		
		
		var num1 =5;
		var num2 =10;
		var total = num1 + num2;
		document.write(total);
		
		
		</script>
		
	</body>

</html>


<input id="q" aria-hidden="true" autocomplete="off" name="q" tabindex="-1" type="url" jsaction="mousedown:ntp.fkbxclk" style="opacity: 0;">
Above input is tag
id is property
"q" is value


driver.findElement(By.id("q"))
Above 
drive is object
findElement is method
By is Class
id is property


Locators:
1. id --Is always has to be unique as per W3 standard
2. name ...this is unique
3. xpath ex. //input[@id='login-signin]
4. cssSelector  ex. #'login-signin
5. linkText
6. partialLinkText
7. className --This can be duplicate
8. tagName


